<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14058">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Art.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4766">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Discuss the following with your counselor: <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/dKM9ZkglGDs?si=coueSTzeFmn89l95" target="_blank"
        >What is Art (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4766 mb-requirement-id-4769">
        (a) What art is and what some of the different forms of art are
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4766 mb-requirement-id-4770">
        (b) The importance of art to humankind
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4766 mb-requirement-id-4771">
        (c) What art means to you and how art can make you feel
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4753">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the following terms and elements of art: line,
      value, shape, form, space, color, and texture. Show examples of each
      element. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/Z-I6o2wu9v4?si=Wq0zT_Pv5G3TcNvP" target="_blank"
        >Beginner's Guide to the 7 Elements of Art (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4772">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor the six principles of design: rhythm, balance,
      proportion, variety, emphasis, and unity. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/qp3jHWyPW-E?si=ARY1F9kOCKWW_ewy" target="_blank"
        >What Makes a Great Design? The 7 Principles You Need to Know (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4756">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Render a subject of your choice in FOUR of these ways: <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/W4NuqLa9i1Q?si=Og8wbpmeGsS3-s73" target="_blank"
        >What Are the Different Mediums Used in Art? (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4757">
        (a) Pen and ink
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4758">
        (b) Watercolors
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4759">
        (c) Pencil
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4760">
        (d) Pastels
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4761">
        (e) Oil paints
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4762">
        (f) Tempera
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4763">
        (g) Acrylics
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4764">
        (h) Charcoal
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4756 mb-requirement-id-4765">
        (i) Computer drawing or painting
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4767">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do ONE of the following: <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://www.tinkercad.com" target="_blank"
        >Design Useful Things website (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.canva.com/" target="_blank"
        >Create With Canva (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/-gbCSnkvwNo" target="_blank"
        >Model and Animate Your Character (video)</a
      >
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4767 mb-requirement-id-4773">
        (a) Design something useful. Make a sketch or model of your design. With
        your counselor's approval, create a promotional piece for the item using
        a picture or pictures.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4767 mb-requirement-id-4774">
        (b) Tell a story with a picture or pictures or using a 3-D rendering.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-4767 mb-requirement-id-4775">
        (c) Design a logo. Share your design with your counselor and explain the
        significance of your logo. Then, with your parent or guardian's
        permission and your counselor's approval, put your logo on Scout
        equipment, furniture, ceramics, or fabric.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4768">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      With your parent or guardian's permission and your counselor's approval,
      visit a museum, art exhibit, art gallery, artists' co-op, or artist's
      workshop. Find out about the art displayed or created there. Discuss what
      you learned with your counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a
        href="https://whichmuseum.com/place/united-states-2682?category%5B%5D=art-design"
        target="_blank"
        >Art Museums in the US (website)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://gocity.com/en/oahu/things-to-do/oahu-for-art-lovers"
        target="_blank"
        >Oahu's Art Scene: Museums, Murals, Makers and More (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-4776">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Find out about three career opportunities in art. Pick one and find out
      the education, training, and experience required for this profession.
      Discuss this with your counselor, and explain why this profession might
      interest you. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/OYF_LHeHLXA?si=5uI1TC_nvDtqMFD3" target="_blank"
        >Careers in Art. The Amazing Jobs an Art Education Can Lead to!
        (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
